by the United Nations'

00:15:40.417 --> 00:15:42.709
Food and Agricultural
Organization,

00:15:42.709 --> 00:15:46.834
or FAO, these are the
top ten rice producing

00:15:46.834 --> 00:15:50.709
countries in the world in 2012.

00:15:52.375 --> 00:15:55.125
Number one is mainland China,

00:15:55.125 --> 00:15:59.999
with 204,285,000 metric tons.

00:16:00.667 --> 00:16:02.083
Number two is India,

00:16:02.083 --> 00:16:06.875
with 152,600,000 metric tons.

00:16:06.999 --> 00:16:09.083
Number three is Indonesia,

00:16:09.083 --> 00:16:14.792
with 69,045,141 metric tons.

00:16:15.333 --> 00:16:16.999
Number four is Vietnam,

00:16:16.999 --> 00:16:22.583
with 43,661,569 metric tons.

00:16:24.166 --> 00:16:25.999
Number five is Thailand,

00:16:25.999 --> 00:16:30.041
with 37,800,000 metric tons.

00:16:30.041 --> 00:16:33.333
Followed by Bangladesh
at number six,

00:16:33.333 --> 00:16:35.250
Myanmar at number seven,

00:16:35.250 --> 00:16:37.208
Philippines at number eight,

00:16:37.208 --> 00:16:38.999
Brazil at number nine,

00:16:38.999 --> 00:16:41.917
and Japan at number ten.

00:16:42.709 --> 00:16:46.208
Manual harvesting and
lack of modern farming

00:16:46.208 --> 00:16:47.999
technology and knowledge

00:16:47.999 --> 00:16:50.750
is a post harvest
problem the FAO,

00:16:50.750 --> 00:16:53.125
and the world bank
is looking into

00:16:53.125 --> 00:16:54.999
and aiming to solve.

00:16:54.999 --> 00:16:57.750
According to a World
Bank-FAO study,

00:16:57.750 --> 00:17:01.375
eight to 26 percent of
rice is lost each year

00:17:01.375 --> 00:17:03.875
in rice producing
developing countries

00:17:03.875 --> 00:17:06.834
because of poor
transportation infrastructure,

00:17:06.834 --> 00:17:08.959
inadequate storage technology,

00:17:08.959 --> 00:17:12.792
and supply chains, and
farmers' lack of access

00:17:12.792 --> 00:17:14.917
to retail markets.

00:17:16.041 --> 00:17:19.041
These post harvest
losses pose a threat

00:17:19.041 --> 00:17:21.458
to global food security.

00:17:21.458 --> 00:17:24.792
The World Bank-FAO study
also estimates that

00:17:24.792 --> 00:17:27.542
these green losses
experienced by developing

00:17:27.542 --> 00:17:31.041
countries such as India,
is already equivalent

00:17:31.041 --> 00:17:34.667
to 89 billion US
dollars worth of income.

00:17:34.667 --> 00:17:37.333
Also, if these grain
losses are collected

00:17:37.333 --> 00:17:39.999
and saved, India alone
will have enough rice

00:17:39.999 --> 00:17:44.417
grains to feed 70 million
to 100 million people

00:17:44.417 --> 00:17:46.125
for a year.

00:17:46.750 --> 00:17:49.999
Rice is a major key in
global food security

00:17:49.999 --> 00:17:53.375
since it is a staple food
in many Asian countries,

00:17:53.375 --> 00:17:55.999
and especially now
that consumption in the

00:17:55.999 --> 00:17:58.999
United States has
seen a steady increase

00:17:58.999 --> 00:18:01.999
in the last 25 years.

00:18:04.125 --> 00:18:06.959
Aside from being a staple
carbohydrate source

00:18:06.959 --> 00:18:11.291
of Asian people, rice
also has other uses.

00:18:11.417 --> 00:18:14.083
Ground rice, or rice
flower, is used in beer

00:18:14.083 --> 00:18:16.542
and wine production,
and in other traditional

00:18:16.542 --> 00:18:20.500
beverages such as
the Japanese amazake,

00:18:20.500 --> 00:18:23.959
and the South American horchata.

00:18:26.875 --> 00:18:29.999
Rice is also now
rivaling maize and wheat

00:18:29.999 --> 00:18:32.999
in the production of
infant food and formula,

00:18:32.999 --> 00:18:36.417
snack food, and
breakfast cereals.

00:18:39.583 --> 00:18:42.583
Rice is gluten free,
so it's a very good

00:18:42.583 --> 00:18:45.750
substitute for people
with gluten intolerance,

00:18:45.750 --> 00:18:48.792
and it is now used
as a main ingredient

00:18:48.792 --> 00:18:51.333
for face powders.

00:18:54.625 --> 00:18:57.417
Rice powder is also
now used as a polishing

00:18:57.417 --> 00:19:01.250
agent for camera
lenses and jewelry.

00:19:01.750 --> 00:19:04.250
Discarded rice
straws are still used

00:19:04.250 --> 00:19:05.875
in rope and paper making,

00:19:05.875 --> 00:19:09.291
and as cattle feed in
many parts of Asia.

00:19:12.166 --> 00:19:14.999
Though it is used in
some non-food items,

00:19:14.999 --> 00:19:18.333
rice remains to be an
important food crop,

00:19:18.333 --> 00:19:20.333
but according to the
International Rice

00:19:20.333 --> 00:19:23.291
Research Institute
in the Philippines,

00:19:23.291 --> 00:19:25.667
in order for mankind
to benefit from this

00:19:25.667 --> 00:19:27.917
grain in the years to come,

00:19:27.917 --> 00:19:30.291
it needs to be biofortified with

00:19:30.291 --> 00:19:32.583
essential nutrients and minerals

00:19:32.583 --> 00:19:34.792
such as iron, and zinc.

00:19:34.792 --> 00:19:36.583
The institute is
currently conducting

00:19:36.583 --> 00:19:39.999
biofortification projects,
not just to increase

00:19:39.999 --> 00:19:43.458
rice's micronutrient
value, but to also

00:19:43.458 --> 00:19:46.999
develop high-yielding varieties.

00:19:48.999 --> 00:19:51.999
Rice may not be as
versatile as wheat

00:19:51.999 --> 00:19:54.667
in terms of end products
and by-products,

00:19:54.667 --> 00:19:57.166
but the daily meals of
the majority of Asian

00:19:57.166 --> 00:19:59.542
families will never
be complete without

00:19:59.542 --> 00:20:03.999
a bowl of hot, steamy rice
on their dinner tables.

00:20:07.625 --> 00:20:09.999
(gentle music)

00:20:13.709 --> 00:20:16.333
Aside from its
color, white, brown,

00:20:16.333 --> 00:20:20.125
or red, rice is also
distinguished according to its

00:20:20.125 --> 00:20:24.999
grain length, long,
medium, and short.

00:20:25.375 --> 00:20:28.250
The long grains tend to
retain their individual

00:20:28.250 --> 00:20:31.999
shape after cooking,
and the medium grains

00:20:31.999 --> 00:20:34.083
become sticky.

00:20:34.834 --> 00:20:38.000
Because of the sticky
texture of medium grains,

00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:41.750
they are commonly used
in risotto in Italy,

00:20:41.750 --> 00:20:44.583
in arros negre in Spain,

00:20:44.583 --> 00:20:47.166
and in sushi in Japan.

00:20:47.750 --> 00:20:49.999
Short grains are
usually cooked into

00:20:49.999 --> 00:20:51.999
rice puddings.

00:20:51.999 --> 00:20:54.500
Since many are
switching to brown rice,

00:20:54.500 --> 00:20:57.875
here is its basic
cooking method.

00:20:57.875 --> 00:20:59.750
Combine one cup of brown rice

00:20:59.750 --> 00:21:02.999
and two cups of
water in a sauce pan.

00:21:02.999 --> 00:21:05.583
Cover it and bring it to a boil.

00:21:05.583 --> 00:21:07.375
Once boiling, reduce the heat

00:21:07.375 --> 00:21:11.250
and let it simmer
for 44 to 50 minutes.

00:21:11.250 --> 00:21:13.250
Unless you're making a risotto,

00:21:13.250 --> 00:21:15.500
do not stir, because
stirring will

00:21:15.500 --> 00:21:18.125
release extra starch.

00:21:18.125 --> 00:21:20.333
Aside from the
conventional risotto,

00:21:20.333 --> 00:21:21.999
and porridge recipes,

00:21:21.999 --> 00:21:25.375
here are two unique
recipes you can try

00:21:25.375 --> 00:21:27.542
using rice.

00:21:27.667 --> 00:21:30.166
The first is Rice Mango Pudding.

00:21:30.166 --> 00:21:31.999
For this recipe you will need

00:21:31.999 --> 00:21:34.542
100 grams of short grain rice,

00:21:34.542 --> 00:21:36.999
50 grams of castor sugar,

00:21:36.999 --> 00:21:39.875
800 milliliters of coconut milk,

00:21:39.875 --> 00:21:41.250
one ripe mango,

00:21:41.250 --> 00:21:44.041
three table spoons of
dairy-free margarine,

00:21:44.041 --> 00:21:47.083
three table spoons
of light brown sugar,

00:21:47.083 --> 00:21:49.999
and two tablespoons
of orange juice.

00:21:51.166 --> 00:21:53.333
First, in an ovenproof dish,

00:21:53.333 --> 00:21:57.917
combine rice, castor
sugar, and coconut milk,

00:21:57.917 --> 00:22:00.999
and bake at 120 degrees Celcius,

00:22:00.999 --> 00:22:03.667
or 250 degrees Fahrenheit,

00:22:03.667 --> 00:22:05.999
for two and a half hours.

00:22:05.999 --> 00:22:09.583
Sir every half hour
to avoid clumping.

00:22:10.333 --> 00:22:13.542
Second, while the
rice is in the oven

00:22:13.542 --> 00:22:15.125
you can make the sauce.

00:22:15.125 --> 00:22:18.709
Peel the mango, and
slice into small cubes,

00:22:18.709 --> 00:22:20.041
then set aside.

00:22:20.041 --> 00:22:22.375
In a small saucepan,
put the margarine,

00:22:22.375 --> 00:22:24.750
brown sugar, and orange juice,

00:22:24.750 --> 00:22:27.250
and put it over
low heat until the

00:22:27.250 --> 00:22:28.875
margarine melts.

00:22:28.875 --> 00:22:31.375
Add the mango cubes,
and let the mixture

00:22:31.375 --> 00:22:33.709
simmer for ten minutes.

00:22:33.709 --> 00:22:36.000
Cool it, transfer to a bowl,

00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:38.625
and use a stick
blender to transform

00:22:38.625 --> 00:22:41.333
into a smooth sauce.

00:22:43.083 --> 00:22:45.667
And third, remove
the rice pudding

00:22:45.667 --> 00:22:48.999
from the oven, stir
well, and spoon into

00:22:48.999 --> 00:22:50.667
small serving bowls.

00:22:50.667 --> 00:22:53.542
Pour the mango
sauce on each bowl,

00:22:53.542 --> 00:22:55.875
and serve.

00:22:56.999 --> 00:22:58.959
The second recipe is a cooling

00:22:58.959 --> 00:23:01.417
Colombian Rice Beverage.

00:23:01.417 --> 00:23:03.875
You will need 50 grams of rice,

00:23:03.875 --> 00:23:05.166
one cup of water,

00:23:05.166 --> 00:23:06.959
three cinnamon sticks,

00:23:06.959 --> 00:23:08.999
four table spoons of sugar,

00:23:08.999 --> 00:23:10.333
one liter of water,

00:23:10.333 --> 00:23:13.583
and 150 grams of
sliced pineapple.

00:23:14.999 --> 00:23:17.333
Making it is very easy.

00:23:17.999 --> 00:23:20.625
First, cook the rice
in one cup of water

00:23:20.625 --> 00:23:24.291
with the cinnamon
sticks to infuse flavor.

00:23:24.999 --> 00:23:28.083
One cooked, removed
the cinnamon sticks,

00:23:28.083 --> 00:23:30.917
and transfer rice to a blender.

00:23:30.917 --> 00:23:33.417
Add the sugar and
one liter of water,

00:23:33.417 --> 00:23:35.709
and then blend until smooth.

00:23:35.709 --> 00:23:38.000
In a tall glass,
put some ice cubes,

00:23:38.000 --> 00:23:40.875
pieces of pineapple,
and pour the rice

00:23:40.875 --> 00:23:42.999
mixture up to the brim.

00:23:42.999 --> 00:23:44.750
This can be served with cookies,

00:23:44.750 --> 00:23:47.792
cornbread, and cheese breads.

00:23:50.250 --> 00:23:52.583
Different countries may
have varying recipes

00:23:52.583 --> 00:23:56.999
using rice, but one fact
is common for all of them.

00:23:56.999 --> 00:23:59.375
And that is they owe
their daily strength

00:23:59.375 --> 00:24:02.083
and nourishment to
this ancient grain

00:24:02.083 --> 00:24:03.583
called rice.

00:24:03.583 --> 00:24:07.999
(gentle music)